# WordPress Rules

## Read-Only Integration
WordPress is the ONLY content source. Never mutate, migrate, or duplicate content.

## Query Pattern
```typescript
// lib/wordpress/queries/get-{entity}.ts
export const GET_QUERY = gql`...`;
export async function getEntity() {
  const data = await wpClient.request(GET_QUERY, variables);
  return data.nodes.map(mapEntity);
}
```

## Requirements
- Use `graphql-request` with singleton client in `client.ts`
- Use fragments for reusable field selections
- Cursor-based pagination (`first`/`after`)
- Map raw responses via `lib/wordpress/mappers/`
- Render Gutenberg HTML through `ContentRenderer` with sanitization

## Environment
- `WORDPRESS_GRAPHQL_URL` — server-side only, never `NEXT_PUBLIC_`

## Error Handling
- Call `notFound()` when slug returns null
- Log GraphQL errors server-side; show user-friendly fallback
